The paper discusses the use of federated learning for medical image analysis, which is a topic that falls under computer science and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the development of a new FL framework, which suggests that it belongs to the "Learning" sub-category (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and medical imaging (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.CR, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
